The paper deals with the use of phasor measurement units (PMUs) in identifying locations of power line outages, which is a problem in the field of power systems engineering. However, the paper proposes a framework and algorithm for identifying multiple outages in the presence of bad data, which involves techniques from signal processing, machine learning, and control systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) for the algorithm design and implementation aspects. The paper also involves networked systems and communication, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
